Fix invokestatic on interfaces in JDK 9+ and begin emitting Java 8 bytecode to support it (#155)

This is necessary for https://github.com/cglib/cglib/commit/380ef56d63756e0a26cce2f8016b3d949482907d to work properly on all JDKs
bump snapshot version
specify release version numbers

Use invokestatic on static interface methods (#153)

Even though they are methods on an interface type, invokeinterface is only for instance method. This code was added >15 years ago, long before static methods were allowed on interfaces.

Treat invokeinterface bridges similarly to invokespecial (#142)

* Treat invokeinterface bridges similarly to invokespecial

In both cases we need to avoid using invokesuper. For interface bridges,
using invokesuper will fail since the method being bridged to is in a
superinterface, not a superclass.

Starting in Java 8, javac emits default bridge methods in interfaces,
which use invokeinterface to bridge to the target method.

Without this fix, the included test case fails with:

```
Caused by: java.lang.NoSuchMethodError: java.lang.Object.f(Ljava/lang/Object;)V
    at B$$EnhancerByCGLIB$$7aa3e8e0.f(<generated>)
    ... 28 more
```

was non-empty.

The mistake was detected by
http://errorprone.info/bugpattern/SizeGreaterThanOrEqualsZero.
